-- Okah Says He Was Asked by Jonathan to Have Mend Rebels Retract Claims
-- B y   R o n   D e r b y
-- 2010-10-15T12:49:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/okah-says-he-was-asked-by-jonathan-to-have-mend-rebels-retract-claims.html
Henry Okah, the man whom the
Nigerian government says is a rebel leader, told the Magistrates
Court in Johannesburg today that Nigerian president Goodluck
Jonathan asked him to tell the rebel group MEND to retract its
claim of responsibility for bomb blasts so that he could blame
political opponents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ron Derby in Johannesburg at 
 rderby1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
